gomodel:SYNGO_897  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: In inhibitory olfactory bulb synapses, the neurexin-3a/b deletion caused a selective decrease in presynaptic GABA release (Fig. 7) without a change in postsynaptic receptor composition (Fig. 6).\n\n1/11/2017 Pim\n- The paper uses DKO of neurexin-3alpha and neurexin-3beta genes (Fig.6/7) Data on the neurexin-3alpha is also included in Supplementary Fig. 2. Overall, the data for this paper directly supports a role for neurexin-3alpha, and a IGI relation of neurexin-3beta that is based on supposed functional redundancy between paralogs and author intent.\n- Authors note: '\"The constitutive ablation of Nrxn3α phenocopied the GABA release phenotype observed in Nrxn3α/β cKO cultured olfactory bulb neurons, suggesting that only Nrxn3α is essential for GABA release in granule cell neurons\". Experimental description: Conditional KO mice were studied" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0912-1514" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3670-7863" ;
        dc:date           "2018-03-19" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_897" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

